<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="172" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,752,1319]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1004,1030]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Remarks</emphasis>
: Described from 
<collectingCountry box="[508,588,1004,1030]" name="Turkey" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[645,707,1004,1030]" name="Israel" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Israel</collectingCountry>
(Aubert 1980). This species is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1352,1436,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Ophion</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the rounded right angled pleurosternal angles, the mandibular teeth, which lack internal angles (often heavily worn), the relatively densely punctate face and mesopleuron and the often quite typical colouration with the body reddish brown with the inner and outer orbits, subalar prominence and two elongate spots in front of the scutellum whitish-yellow. The numerous flagellomeres (59‒63) are comparatively stout. Study of the 
<typeStatus box="[1307,1405,1148,1174]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hedwig, 1961" authorityName="Hedwig" authorityYear="1961" box="[151,675,1184,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="mocsaryi" variety="decedens">
<emphasis box="[151,347,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Ophion mocsaryi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[404,507,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">decedens</emphasis>
Hedwig, 1961
</taxonomicName>
shows that it is conspecific with the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aubert" authorityYear="1980" box="[1188,1313,1184,1210]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipictor">
<emphasis box="[1188,1313,1184,1210]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">O. bipictor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the name 
<emphasis box="[268,371,1220,1246]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">decedens</emphasis>
was described as a 
<taxonomicName box="[613,742,1220,1246]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" rank="variety" variety="and">variety and</taxonomicName>
published in 
<date box="[905,1069,1220,1246]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" value="1961-04-01">
April 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[989,1000,1220,1234]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">st</superScript>
1961
</date>
, which means that the name is unavailable according to the code. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hedwig" authorityYear="1961" box="[546,901,1256,1283]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="mocsaryi" status="syn. nov." variety="decedens">
<emphasis box="[546,741,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">Ophion mocsaryi</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[798,901,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">decedens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[908,1010,1257,1283]" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">syn. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is therefore considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aubert" authorityYear="1980" box="[182,305,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="172" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipictor">
<emphasis box="[182,305,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="172">O. bipictor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
